Tech For Trump
--------------

From The Information ( https://www.theinformation.com/articles/marc-andrees=
sen-ben-horowitz-say-they-plan-to-donate-to-trump-pac ) :

Marc Andreessen and Ben Horowitz, who run one of Silicon Valley=E2=80=99s m=
ost prominent venture capital firms, have told the firm=E2=80=99s employees=
 in recent days they plan to make large donations to political action commi=
ttees supporting the election of Donald Trump, people familiar with the mat=
ter said. The planned donations by Andreessen and Horowitz, who run the epo=
nymous VC firm behind influential startups like OpenAI, SpaceX and Anduril,=
 would add to the number of big-name tech investors and executives that hav=
e lined up to support the former president. Neither Andreessen or Horowitz =
have previously said publicly they would support Trump.

That was rectified shortly thereafter, when Andreessen and Horowitz release=
d a podcast ( https://pmarca.substack.com/p/new-podcast-little-tech-agenda-=
the ) explicitly endorsing President Trump and explaining their rationale; =
a day earlier Elon Musk announced significant financial support ( https://w=
ww.wsj.com/politics/elections/elon-musk-has-said-he-is-committing-around-45=
-million-a-month-to-a-new-pro-trump-super-pac-dda53823 ) of Trump=E2=80=99s=
 campaign, after explicitly endorsing him ( https://x.com/elonmusk/status/1=
812256998588662068 ) on Saturday shortly after the former president narrowl=
y escaped assassination.

Musk=E2=80=99s increasingly conservative turn has been well documented, by =
Musk himself on his prolific X account. What is worth pointing out is that =
from an analytical viewpoint, which considers Musk=E2=80=99s personal and b=
usiness interests, this is an entirely rational and understandable shift. T=
he Biden administration famously excluded Tesla from its electric vehicle i=
nitiatives ( https://x.com/elonmusk/status/1812256998588662068 ) , probably=
