This hearing only emphasized this point, and, to be frank, the New York Pos=
t episode has only added credence to the Republican=E2=80=99s argument (mor=
eover, the degree to which Democrats exhorted the three CEOs to act more fo=
rcefully =E2=80=94 in their favor, of course =E2=80=94 only augmented said =
argument). Tech as a whole does itself a disservice dismissing what these h=
earings represent with a hand-wave of =E2=80=9Csame old same old=E2=80=9D; =
the industry is running out of allies in government, and it is their natura=
l allies, the Republicans, that increasingly have the more compelling argum=
ent about tech=E2=80=99s power going too far.

This is how you end up with a Republican vice-presidential candidate strong=
ly supporting the current FTC=E2=80=99s aggressive attempts to prosecute bi=
g tech for antitrust violations ( https://stratechery.com/2024/jd-vance-and=
